        "title": "Honeypot Spam Filter",
        "excerpt":"This is a spam filtering technique where we put a hidden field into the form. A human can’t see it and it’s not required. &lt;!--We use the following to tell netlify what we are doing and what field is the honeypot--&gt;     &lt;form class=\"form-template-v3\" method=\"POST\" netlify-honeypot=\"bot-field\" data-netlify=\"true\"&gt;&lt;!--This is the field. --&gt;          &lt;p class=\"hidden\" style=\"display:none\"&gt;            &lt;label&gt;Don’t fill this out if you're human: &lt;input name=\"bot-field\" /&gt;&lt;/label&gt;          &lt;/p&gt; However a bot WILL fill it in. Then we know it’s spam.  It’s a lot eaiser on the user than using a captcha. ","categories": ["Form Processing"],
